{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fully fund sign language lessons for parents of deaf children in early years.",
        "additional_details": "At present, deaf children and their parents have no way of learning British sign language unless they approach a charity and are lucky enough to find availability on courses. Or the families can pay hefty price tags to learn British sign language with level 1 of 8 Courses costing up to \u00a3350, with a price increase per level. \r\n\r\nParents of deaf children can struggle on a daily basis to communicate effectively with their children. \r\n\r\nFrankly, we cant believe this isn't already in place.",
        "background": "We are asking that the Government make full British Sign Language lessons accessible by fully funding for the parents of deaf children in the early years of their child\u2019s life.",
